The paper discusses the combination of trusted execution environments (TEEs) with blockchains, which involves security and privacy concerns. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes an architecture and prototype for smart-contract execution within Intel SGX technology for Hyperledger Fabric, which is a platform for enterprise blockchain applications. This involves software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY) aspects.
